HB 1174 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Bourriaque
Abstract: Re-creates the Louisiana Department of Transportation and Development.
Present law (sunset) provides that the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) and
all the statutory entities made a part of the dept. by law must begin to terminate their
operations on June 30, 2026, and that all legislative authority for such entities shall cease as
of July 1, 2027, unless the legislature enacts a bill recreating the DOTD, and its statutory
entities prior thereto.
